&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assembler – Production (Boise, ID)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full‑Time • Non‑Exempt • On‑Site • Day Shift (5:00am–3:30pm M-TH) and Night Shift (3:00pm-1:30am M-TH) Overtime on Friday as needed&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Multiquip is seeking a hands‑on, safety‑focused Assembler to support the build and testing of high‑quality machinery and equipment. In this role, you’ll work with prints, tools, and mechanical components to ensure products are assembled accurately, efficiently, and to the highest standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you enjoy mechanical work, problem‑solving, and contributing to a fast‑moving production environment, this is a great opportunity to make an impact within an established, industry‑leading organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assemble machines, equipment, and sub‑assemblies following prints, specifications, and verbal instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow detailed assembly procedures to ensure accuracy and consistency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove small amounts of metal to achieve precise fit between parts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drill, tap, or ream holes as required by the build process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align components and secure them using bolts, screws, or rivets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install moving parts (shafts, levers, bearings) and test for smooth, proper movement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support testing and analysis of completed products to ensure performance and safety.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Read and interpret prints, wiring diagrams, and assembly documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely operate hoists, hydraulic presses, forklifts, and power buggies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fuel and test completed products or assist during final testing processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle machinery and tools with care and attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform additional duties as assigned to support production needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain regular and predictable attendance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience &amp;amp; Education&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands‑on mechanical experience; hydraulic system familiarity preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School diploma or GED.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate hand tools and air‑powered tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to safely operate hoists.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication &amp;amp; Interpersonal Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read and understand simple instructions, numbers, and measurements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear, basic communication skills for working within a production team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reliable, safety‑minded work habits with strong attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to perform basic math (addition, subtraction, measurement in feet/inches).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated skill in fitting, aligning, and assembling mechanical parts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to recognize part variances or issues and report concerns promptly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with mechanical testing or functional checks is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Computer Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read from electronic or printed diagrams or instructions if needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic comfort learning internal systems or documentation tools (training provided).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Certificates, Licenses &amp;amp; Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
