&lt;h2&gt;Concrete Application Specialist (Texas Region)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full‑Time • Exempt • Field‑Based in Texas / Extensive Travel&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Multiquip is seeking an experienced and driven &lt;strong&gt;Concrete Application Specialist (CAS)&lt;/strong&gt; to champion MQ Whiteman concrete placement and finishing equipment across assigned territories. This highly visible, field‑based role blends hands‑on product demonstrations, contractor engagement, and business development to drive demand and expand our presence beyond traditional rental and distribution channels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re a concrete industry expert who enjoys working directly on job sites, showcasing equipment in real‑world conditions, and building trusted relationships with contractors, this is an exciting opportunity to make a measurable impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Business Development &amp;amp; Customer Engagement&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prospect and develop new concrete business by calling directly on end users and contractors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cultivate strong contractor relationships to generate pull‑through sales at job sites.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain databases of key contractor contacts and stay informed of major construction activity within assigned regions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate frequently with District Sales Representatives, Product Managers, and Multiquip leadership to ensure a unified customer approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Product Demonstrations &amp;amp; Technical Expertise&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highlight, demonstrate, and market MQ Whiteman concrete placement and finishing equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely conduct live product demonstrations—day or night—in construction and industrial environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explain equipment features, benefits, and value propositions clearly and confidently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize company‑provided marketing materials to recommend the right machine for each application.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Market Intelligence &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate job‑site successes, challenges, competitive strategies, and pricing insights to management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete regular reporting through HubSpot CRM, including detailed market information and customer call reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share customer and market feedback to support continuous improvement in product design and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Equipment &amp;amp; Asset Management&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain, transport, and securely store consigned (demo) equipment in company vehicle, trailer, residence, or approved secure locations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate equipment consignment to contractors or authorized distributors as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promptly report changes in consigned equipment status (e.g., sale conversions or storage relocations).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure company‑issued vehicle and trailer are maintained in roadworthy condition and secured during transport.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain DOT standards and compliance requirements at all times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Events &amp;amp; Brand Representation&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in national and regional trade shows, industry meetings, and promotional events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote the full range of Multiquip products, parts, maintenance, and service offerings—engaging additional sales team members when appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exercise sound judgment when entertaining customers and submit expenses in accordance with company policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You Bring&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Experience &amp;amp; Education&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or GED required.&lt;/li&gt;
