&lt;h2&gt;Mechanical Assembler II – Power Equipment&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full‑Time • Non‑Exempt • On‑Site (Fullerton, CA) • Monday–Friday (Overtime as Needed)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a skilled and detail‑oriented &lt;strong&gt;Mechanical Assembler II&lt;/strong&gt; to support the mechanical assembly and disassembly of generators and other MQ power and construction products. In this hands‑on role, you’ll perform mid‑level assembly work on generators, pumps, concrete mixers, and related equipment, using technical documentation to ensure precision, quality, and safety throughout the build and refurbishment process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you enjoy working with mechanical systems, take pride in accurate workmanship, and thrive in a fast‑paced manufacturing or refurbishment environment, this role offers an opportunity to contribute directly to high‑quality equipment production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Mechanical Assembly &amp;amp; Refurbishment&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform mechanical disassembly and reassembly of generators, including DCA units, studio refurbishments, and container refurbishments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assemble, modify, fit, and align equipment and components using drilling, grinding, mounting, and fastening techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support subassembly builds such as pumps, mixers, trailers, and related equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean, lubricate, and maintain parts, components, and subassemblies during the build process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply labels, nameplates, and identifying markings to completed units.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Technical Interpretation &amp;amp; Precision Work&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Read and interpret blueprints, assembly instructions, and technical specifications to determine proper methods and build sequences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drill, tap, ream, and countersink holes using hand tools, power tools, and drill presses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform minor electrical wiring and soldering as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather, stage, and prepare parts, tools, materials, and subassemblies for assigned work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Quality, Inspection &amp;amp; Troubleshooting&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspect assemblies to ensure compliance with specifications, tolerances, and customer requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify issues, troubleshoot mechanical problems, and make necessary adjustments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow all quality control procedures to maintain high standards of workmanship.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Collaboration, Safety &amp;amp; Leadership Support&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate forklifts, hoists, and small cranes to safely move and position equipment and materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with inventory monitoring and production needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train, mentor, and support Level I Assemblers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a safe, clean, and organized work environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in team meetings, training sessions, and safety briefings as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Additional Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned to support operational and production goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You Bring&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Experience &amp;amp; Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of mechanical assembly experience, preferably in a manufacturing or refurbishment environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency with hand tools, power tools, forklifts, and small cranes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read and interpret blueprints, schematics, and technical drawings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of mechanical systems; minor electrical wiring and soldering experience preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic math skills for measurements, layouts, and calculations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;S

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;National Sales Coordinator – Sales Support &amp;amp; Customer Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-Time • Non-Exempt • Office-Based • Monday–Friday (Hybrid)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a detail-oriented and customer-focused &lt;strong&gt;National Sales Coordinator&lt;/strong&gt; to join our team. In this fast-paced, high-volume role, you will serve as a key point of contact for customers and the Outside Sales team—managing inbound inquiries, processing orders, and ensuring a seamless customer experience from quote to delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you thrive in a dynamic environment, enjoy multitasking, and take pride in delivering exceptional service while maintaining accuracy, this is a great opportunity to make a meaningful impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary contact for a high volume of inbound customer and Outside Sales inquiries related to product availability, pricing, order status, invoices, and order processing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and enter customer quotations into SAP, ensuring accuracy in pricing, product availability, and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately process sales orders, including pricing, payment terms, freight terms, and delivery timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate order confirmations and proactively notify customers of any updates or changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor open orders and backorders; follow up regularly to ensure accurate lead times and timely customer communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate closely with inventory and supply chain teams to resolve held or delayed orders and provide detailed updates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Outside Sales representatives to support customer accounts and maintain strong internal collaboration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve customer issues and inquiries promptly, professionally, and with a solutions-oriented mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a strong working knowledge of company products and equipment to effectively support customers and sales initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform additional duties as assigned to support business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience &amp;amp; Education&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or equivalent required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of experience in customer service, sales support, or order processing in a high-volume environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in a call center or similar fast-paced setting preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication &amp;amp; Interpersonal Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to professionally engage with customers, sales teams, and cross-functional departments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer-first mindset with strong problem-resolution abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical &amp;amp; Systems Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Microsoft Office, particularly Excel and Word.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with SAP or similar ERP systems preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to learn and navigate internal systems and product information quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational &amp;amp; Organizational Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly detail-oriented with strong multitasking and time management abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple priorities and meet deadlines in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with sound decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Qualifications&lt;/stro

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join our team and help keep production running smoothly! As a Paint Assistant on our Powder Coat Paint Line, you’ll play a key role in preparing, painting, and finishing parts to ensure a high-quality final product.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare parts for painting (plug holes, tape, mask surfaces)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hang parts using proper hooks and spacing for optimal coating&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspect finished parts for quality (runs, sags, missed areas)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove parts from the line and stack safely to prevent damage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean and maintain paint line equipment and tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Record wastewater discharge and pH readings as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely operate equipment such as hoists, forklifts, or power buggies (as assigned)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle machinery and materials with care and attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the team with additional duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain regular, reliable attendance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No prior experience required — we’ll train you!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School diploma or GED preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read, write, and follow basic instructions and safety guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic math skills (add, subtract, multiply, divide; understand ratios and measurements)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable using hand tools and air-powered tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate or learn to operate a hoist and material handling equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team player with good communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Physical Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to stand and walk for up to 10 hours per shift&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Frequent use of hands for handling, gripping, and reaching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Occasional bending, kneeling, or crouching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift and move up to 50 lbs regularly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working in a fast-paced, industrial environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work around noise, chemicals, and manufacturing equipment&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;(hearing protection required)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Environment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to industrial materials such as paint, cleaners, fuels, and hydraulic fluids&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Loud environment with required safety equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Repetitive lifting overhead&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safety-focused culture with proper training and PPE provided&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
