&lt;h2&gt;Warehouse / Parts Associate – Power Equipment&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full‑Time • Non‑Exempt • Onsite (Fullerton, CA)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a reliable and detail‑focused &lt;strong&gt;Warehouse / Parts Associate&lt;/strong&gt; to support warehouse and production operations through accurate shipping and receiving, inventory control, and material handling. This role plays a key part in keeping production running smoothly by ensuring materials are properly kitted, staged, stocked, and transacted within SAP.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re hands‑on, safety‑minded, and comfortable working with inventory systems in a manufacturing environment, this position offers a great opportunity to contribute directly to production efficiency and accuracy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Shipping, Receiving &amp;amp; Material Handling&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receive, inspect, and process inbound shipments; unload and store materials in designated locations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare, stage, and load outbound shipments accurately and efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify inbound and outbound shipments for accuracy and damage; document and report discrepancies to the Supervisor or Manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate forklifts and other material‑handling equipment safely to move, stage, load, and store materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pick, pack, crate, label, and ship products in accordance with company and customer requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure correct quantities and product types are shipped based on documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Inventory Control &amp;amp; SAP Transactions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain inventory accuracy through cycle counts, system transactions, and proper material handling practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process inventory movements and updates within SAP to ensure real‑time accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Repackage materials as needed; inspect products and report any damage or quality concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Production Support&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the production floor by printing production orders, pulling and kitting components, and staging materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with light assembly or sub‑assembly builds as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform labeling, sorting, wrapping, and minor pallet repairs to support production and shipping needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Safety, Quality &amp;amp; Housekeeping&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clean, organized, and safe work environment; support warehouse security practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow all company policies, safety standards, and operational procedures at all times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned in support of warehouse and production operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You Bring&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Experience &amp;amp; Education&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or GED required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–3 years of experience in warehouse, manufacturing, or a related environment preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands‑on experience with SAP strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read and interpret safety rules, production orders, and Bills of Materials (BOMs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience operating forklifts and other material‑handling equipment (certification provided or required).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail with a focus on accuracy and quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work effectively both independently and as part of a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Physical Requirements&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The physical demands described here are representative of those required to successfully perform the essential functions of this role. Reasonable accommodations ma

