&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full‑Time • Hourly • On‑Site • Day Shift (5:00am–3:30pm Monday to Thursday, Overtime on Friday as needed)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a skilled &lt;strong&gt;Powder Coat Painter&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;to operate electrostatic painting equipment and ensure high‑quality finishes on metal workpieces. This role uses cone, disk, and nozzle‑type electrostatic systems to apply negatively charged paint particles to positively charged parts.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;As a Powder Coat Painter, you play a key role in keeping parts moving smoothly through our powder coating process. You’ll help ensure high‑quality finishes, safe handling of materials, and consistent production flow in a fast‑paced environment. &amp;nbsp;The ideal candidate is detail‑oriented, safety‑focused, and able to work independently in a fast‑paced production environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Manager – MQ Power (Lifecycle &amp;amp; Operations)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-Time • Exempt • Cypress, CA • Monday–Friday (Hybrid)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Multiquip is seeking a strategic and customer-focused &lt;strong&gt;Product Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to lead and grow our MQ Power product line. In this high-impact role, you’ll own the full product lifecycle—from concept and development to optimization and end-of-life decisions—while driving profitability and market success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re a data-driven, collaborative professional who thrives on bringing products to market and delivering solutions that meet real customer needs, this is an opportunity to make a strong impact with an industry leader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Strategy &amp;amp; Lifecycle Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and manage assigned MQ Power product lines through the full lifecycle, including development, optimization, cost reduction, and end-of-life decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop product strategies, roadmaps, and business plans aligned with company growth objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify new product opportunities through market research, competitive analysis, and customer insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Insight &amp;amp; Customer Focus&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the voice of the customer by understanding application needs across rental, construction, industrial, and end-user segments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure products deliver strong economic value while meeting performance, cost, and profitability targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Voice of Customer (VOC) initiatives to inform product decisions and enhancements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New Product Development &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define product specifications and build business cases for new product introductions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Engineering and cross-functional teams to launch products successfully and on time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support customized product requests (CPRs) by coordinating across Sales, Engineering, and Operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supplier &amp;amp; Partner Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary liaison with suppliers to develop, test, and improve product offerings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Address quality concerns, manage improvements, and support warranty resolution efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance, Pricing &amp;amp; Inventory&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor product performance, warranty trends, and customer feedback to drive continuous improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Supply Chain to manage inventory levels aligned with demand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support pricing strategies to achieve revenue and margin targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Sales, Service, Parts, Marketing, Engineering, and Finance teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide product training and application expertise to internal teams and customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support marketing initiatives, technical documentation, and trade show participation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Intelligence &amp;amp; Communication&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct ongoing competitive analysis and market research&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate product updates, improvements, and key insights across internal teams and external partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience &amp;amp; Educa

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Support Specialist – MQ Power Division&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-Time • Non-Exempt • Remote-In Office&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Specialist – Power Equipment (MQ Power)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full‑Time • Non‑Exempt • Cypress, CA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Multiquip is seeking a highly technical and customer‑focused &lt;strong&gt;Product Specialist – Power Equipment&lt;/strong&gt; to serve as the primary product expert for MQ Power’s mobile diesel generator portfolio and related industrial power products. In this high‑impact role, you’ll provide in‑depth product knowledge and support to customers, dealers, engineers, service centers, parts teams, and internal stakeholders—both pre‑sale and throughout the ownership lifecycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is focused on the &lt;strong&gt;product itself&lt;/strong&gt;—specifications, configurations, documentation, applications, and issue resolution—while partnering closely with Technical Support, Product Management, Engineering, Sales, Parts, and Service teams. You will also play a critical role in coordinating Customized Product Requests (CPRs) and driving a high level of customer ownership satisfaction. If you enjoy being the subject‑matter expert, solving product challenges, and collaborating across teams, this role offers a dynamic and rewarding opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
